Hi @linhdam,

Thanks for the update and fast fix! This is a yes and a no however the edit is fixed so I marked it as fix works. The initial report, the view all reviews one via index.json still works, however the edit vulnerability is fixed.

First regarding the attack complexity requiring IDs, as mentioned in the initial report and the following exploit method, the review IDs are also accessible to the AERI user due to the fact that https://judge.me/index.json is accessible to them (which as mentioned still works now). That means all the prerequisites of the attack are available to the AERI user and no further action from the victims is required. As shown here:

{F2013446}

Now about the Edit vulnerability, I tried it again and I can confirm that the fix works! When I attempt to point to reviews in Judge.Me app it now returns a 404 Not Found response as shown here:

